<br>
To this day, its still not working the way it was designed to work at least to what I have experienced.  But One great thing about it is, I don't have to make arrows for pulling.  I find that Divine Stun works great for pulling mobs.  It has the same range as my primal bow (225ft).  Also, it gets reset when you can't see your target.  It may not do dmg when you cast it but it sure leaves extra room in your inventories for other stuffs.<br>
<br>
/cheer<br>
<br>
Gthany Dragonblade - 60th Crusader of Xegony<br>
Death Knights<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwhitefyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Whitefyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight Of the Realm</span><br>  Posts: 211<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/31/02 2:23:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=98.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Divine Stun - Useful in another way.</span><hr size=1> I use mine for pulling too, but it's working according to the new description. It no longer stuns anything. Just interupts spell casting. I guess that is still a stun, but only for a milisecond. The mob won't stop like you see with other stuns. IMO if a 9 point skill is reduced to be useful for just pulling then it needs some work. <p><BR><BR><A HREF=" http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=77809"><B>Whitefyre Nobleheart</B></A><BR><B><FONT FACE="Old English Text MT, Arial">Paladin of the 60th Light</FONT></B><BR>If I were an Autobot, I'd be:<br>
