  alt="Click to see what Autobot you could be!"></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utaliewin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taliewin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 246<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/31/02 2:28:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=98.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Divine Stun - Useful in another way.</span><hr size=1> There is talk they are thinking of raising the stun cap to level 60 for all classes, and Divine Stun to mobs 60+. What this would mean is that 60+ mobs still could not be stunned (normal stun rules apply), only have their spells interrupted.  And in high end encounters, that I would think is the only reason you would use stun anyway?<br>
<br>
So in its current form it is somewhat useless, except to interupt spell casting of mobs 55-60. But if they do change the stun cap, then it would be very useful.<br>
<br>
